The Zipkin Kafka collector supports receiving batches of spans instead of single spans after https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin/pull/995. However, having a py_zipkin user implement batching solely in the transport_handler seems like it'd be too difficult on their part. 

Maybe we could support having `ZipkinLoggingContext` take a batch_size param that defaults to something large but sane (20?), then in [log_spans](https://github.com/Yelp/py_zipkin/blob/8c03eac8b0d49fa64d644bef62edbfc044078bb1/py_zipkin/logging_helper.py#L75) we could call transport_handler with a list of thrift-encoded spans as opposed to a single span at a time.

@kaisen, thoughts?

